expectation: S249 found 99.3% non-compliant (276/278). Predict: check_mode 70-85%, intent/progress near-universal. expect/actual/diff sparse (10-25%). ~1-3 fully compliant lanes. Artifact coverage ~30-50%.
method: Sampled all non-ABANDONED lanes from tasks/SWARM-LANES.md. Checked Etc column for key=value pairs matching 9 required fields: intent, progress, blocked, next_step, check_mode, artifact, expect, actual, diff.
population_note: S325 ABANDONED sweep collapsed active lane count from 278 (S249 baseline) to 9 non-ABANDONED lanes. Comparison is structurally different: S249 measured 278 legacy lanes (mostly schema-less); S328 measures 9 post-sweep lanes (recently touched, schema-aware).
interpretation: Large apparent improvement vs S249 is partially a survivor bias artifact: the S325 ABANDONED sweep removed 269 stale schema-less lanes, leaving only 9 recently-touched lanes that were written after schema awareness increased. The surviving population is NOT representative of the pre-sweep state. True signal: post-sweep lanes still have two persistent gaps. (1) artifact= compliance is only 22.2% — lanes close without recording experiment file references. (2) expect/actual/diff triple compliance is only 22.2% — the expect-act-diff primitive is still not consistently embedded at lane creation, only sometimes added at closure. intent/progress/blocked are now near-universal (100%). The enforcement gap is in the post-hoc evidence fields, not the status fields.
key_finding: Post-sweep lanes show 100% compliance on identity fields (intent/progress/blocked) but only 22% compliance on evidence fields (artifact, expect+actual+diff). The self-model contract is half-adopted: agents declare intent but rarely record evidence inline.
next_actions: Embed artifact= and expect= in lane-creation template (not just at closure)
Add actual= and diff= to close_lane.py auto-prompt
F-META1 remains open: schema drift risk returns when new bulk lanes are created
